Invention:  Vaccine
Year:       1796
Inventor:   Edward Jenner
Country:    England
Category:   Medicine
Description:Cowpox inoculation against smallpox
Impact:     Saved billions; smallpox eradicated; immunology foundation

Invention:  Internet
Year:       1969
Inventor:   DARPA/UCLA
Country:    USA
Category:   Communication
Description:Packet-switched network connecting computers
Impact:     Became internet; most transformative network ever

Invention:  World Wide Web
Year:       1989
Inventor:   Tim Berners-Lee
Country:    UK/Switzerland
Category:   Communication
Description:Hyperlinked documents over internet
Impact:     Democratized information; e-commerce; social media

